<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Non-Bearer-Contact Press" class="currentChild" href="Non-Bearer-Contact_Press">Non-Bearer-Contact Press</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A type of printing press used in <a title="Offset Lithography" href="Offset_Lithography">offset lithography</a> in which the blanket and plate cylinder <a title="Bearer" href="Bearer">bearer</a>s (metal rings located at each end of each cylinder body, with diameters greater than the diameter of the cylinder body itself) do not contact each other while the press is in operation. Whether a press is a non-bearer-contact press or a <a title="Bearer-Contact Press" href="Bearer-Contact_Press">bearer-contact press</a> affects proper cylinder setting and <a title="Packing" href="Packing">packing</a> considerations. See <a title="Bearer" href="Bearer">Bearer</a>, <a title="Plate Cylinder" href="Plate_Cylinder">Plate Cylinder</a>, <a title="Blanket Cylinder" href="Blanket_Cylinder">Blanket Cylinder</a>, and <a title="Packing" href="Packing">Packing</a>. 
</p>
